    "summary": "(A) A selective bibliography:\n\n-- Lambda-conversion and Logic, 1981 - Drukkerij Elinkwijk [book: PhD Diss., Utrecht, 1981]\n\n-- On a Theorem of Tarski - Libertas Math, 1982 [paper]\n\n-- A Bibliography of Lambda-calculi, Combinatory Logics and Related Topics, 1982 - Mathematisch Centrum [CWI], Amsterdam [booklet]\n\n-- Abstract AUTOMATH - CWI Syllabi, 1983 - KNAW Narcis [= Mathematisch Centrum / CWI, Amsterdam: Mathematical Centre Tract 160] [book]\n\n-- Semantics for Classical AUTOMATH and Related Systems [PDF] from kun.nl - Information and control, 1983 [paper -- NB joint author: Henk Barendregt -- whence... Erd\u00f6s number 4 (!): H. P. Barendregt - A. M. Cohen - P. J. Cameron - P. Erd\u00f6s]\n\n-- Impredicative Type Theories, 1986 - Katholieke Universiteit Nijmegen [= KUN] [monograph]\n\n-- Propositions-As-Types Revisited,1986 - Department of Informatics [KUN] [monograph section]\n\n-- Semantics of Constructive Type Theory I, 1987 - Department of Informatics [KUN] [monograph section \u2013 also issued as a separate paper in Libertas Math. 1986]\n\n-- Varieties of Generalized Functionality (Generalized Polymorphism 1),1987 - Department of Informatics [KUN] [monograph section]\n\n-- Constructions and Propositional Types I: (Generalized Polymorphism 3), 1987 - Department of Informatics [KUN] [monograph section]\n\n-- Classical Proofs: Lambda Calculus Methods in Elementary Proof Theory, 1990 [Nijmegen Lecture Notes]\n\n-- Beyond BHK, 1993 - extended abstract in: Barendregt, Bezem, and Klop, editors, Dirk van Dalen Festschrift [Utrecht] [monograph -- full text at equivalences.org., 2006]\n\n-- Tarski's Claim - equivalences.org, 2010 = Chapter 13, in: Witness Theory (2020)\n\n-- An Ancient Logic (Chrysippus and His Modern Readers I), Lambert Academic Publishing, Saarbr\u00fccken [December] 2016 [ISBN 978-3-330-01661-3] = Chapter 8 in: Witness Theory (2020)\n\n-- Witness Theory, Notes on \u03bb-calculus and Logic, College Publications, London [Marc